00:29:14,764 --> 00:29:16,045
the 91 is basically just...

561
00:29:16,725 --> 00:29:20,468
take x and divide it by half and then go the same amount to the left or right and that's

562
00:29:20,488 --> 00:29:21,849
your end position for your 91.

563
00:29:22,589 --> 00:29:26,332
And then for the 181, divide x by 4 and double that trajectory.

564
00:29:26,372 --> 00:29:31,595
And we just basically just drew NURB curves on the ground as guidelines and made sure

565
00:29:31,616 --> 00:29:33,357
that we followed the trajectory exactly.

